analysis: The documents primarily consist of executive orders. One executive order addresses vulnerabilities in information and communications technology and services from foreign adversaries, declaring a national emergency. Another focuses on maintaining the confidentiality of classified information and establishing a uniform Federal personnel security program. A third revokes and amends previous executive orders related to sanctions against Iran following the implementation of nuclear-related measures under the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action (JCPOA).
title: Safeguarding Information, Communications, and Security Interests
